{introverse} quick docs


Built-in complete themes in {ggplot2}
get_help() docs


Description

All functions documented here are part of the {ggplot2} package, which is part of the {tidyverse}.

The {ggplot2} package provides several built-in complete themes for styling the overall look of your plot. The default theme used is theme_gray() (aka theme_grey()). You can specify a built-in theme in one of two ways:

  • Use the function ggplot2::theme_set() to change all subsequent plots made during the given R session.
  • Add a given complete theme function to your plot directly to change only that plots complete theme

Available complete themes include the following:

  • theme_gray() aka theme_grey() (The default theme.)
  • theme_bw()
  • theme_linedraw()
  • theme_light()
  • theme_dark()
  • theme_minimal()
  • theme_classic()
  • theme_void()

To use these function, you need to either first load the {ggplot2} library, or always use the function with ggplot2:: notation.

# Load the library
library(ggplot2)
# Or, load the full tidyverse:
library(tidyverse)

# Or, use :: notation, for example with theme_bw()
ggplot2::theme_bw()

Examples

The examples below use the msleep dataset. Learn more about this dataset with get_help("msleep").

# Show the msleep dataset with head()
head(msleep)

# Set the default theme of all subsequent plots to theme_bw(), for example
# Don't forget parentheses!
theme_set(theme_bw())


# Example of a plot using theme_gray (the default)
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  # Optional, since this is the default
  theme_gray()


# Example of a plot using theme_bw()
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_bw()


# Example of a plot using theme_linedraw()
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_linedraw()


# Example of a plot using theme_light()
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_light()


# Example of a plot using theme_dark()
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_dark()


# Example of a plot using theme_minimal()
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_minimal()


# Example of a plot using theme_classic()
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_classic()


# Example of a plot using theme_void()
# This theme is completely blank!
ggplot(msleep) + 
  aes(x = sleep_rem, y = awake) + 
  geom_point() +
  theme_void()
